+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VQT18vDM5ayWCfJMZq815q","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `src/` directory is empty. This is a greenfield project with clear requirements. The design is straightforward — a `TimeTracker` class with persistence to JSON. Given this is a simple, well-defined library, I'll skip the extended brainstorming and move directly to TDD implementation.\n\nNon-interactive mode: using Autopilot. The design decisions are straightforward:\n\n1. **Architecture**: Single `TimeTracker` class — simple, no over-engineering needed\n2. **Persistence**: Synchronous JSON file I/O with `fs` (Node built-in) — simplest approach for a library\n3. **Data model**: Array of `TimeEntry` objects with `taskName`, `startTime`, `endTime` (ISO strings or null)\n4. **API**: `start(name)`, `stop()`, `getEntries(filter?)`, `getSummary()` exported from `src/index.ts`\n\nLet me invoke TDD skill to implement this properly."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1625,"cache_read_input_tokens":21858,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1625},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7fb9180-1202-4517-bb7b-51e50e946a45","uuid":"a617c5b9-cc5c-4799-b57f-6e658b928a1a"}
